Two people have died at a quarry in Matungulu, Machakos county. They were buried alive after the quarry they were working in collapsed on them in Nguluni on Friday. Matungulu police boss Samuel Mukuusi confirmed the incident. "It is true that two people have died at a quarry in Matungulu, we are investigating to know what exactly happened," Mukuusi told theÂ Star on the phone. Eyewitnesses said one of the men died instantly while another succumbed to injuries at Kangundo Level 4 Hospital. The bodies were removed to the same hospital's mortuary. Click here for the latest political news